	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hmmmm.<br><br>With the way the /con and experience system is organized, it gets harder and harder to solo as you get higher in level.&nbsp;&nbsp;At level 36, I have serious trouble with some green casters and have to be very careful selecting blues to take on solo.  And there are certain MOBs that are notorious undercons (did someone day Dorn?  Finally killed THAT jerk for the first time not too long ago).  There are other MOBs that hit very hard for their level and/or have an unusually high amount of Hit Points (most Giants).<br><br>That being said, we get Feign Death at level 17, so we get killed solo *very* rarely, if we're smart.  Getting chain-cast by 3 or more mobs is a problem (I can usually get FD off against 2), as is having FD fail at a bad time.  Of course, if you haven't kept your FD skill level-capped ... well, get to it.<br><br>The beauty of being a monk is that you can go almost everywhere within reason with little trouble.  I used to chuckle to myself every time I made the run from FV to LoIO -- a run that terrifies most other classes.  No sweat for a monk -- a Drachnid aggros you and you just drop and wait a minute.<br><br>You can 'test' MOBs with little risk or having to beg for a SOW so you can run to zone if you get your butt kicked.  Just yesterday I had a very very funny battle against a Frost Giant.  Finally made my first trip to Velious and was making my way from Iceclad to Thurgadin for a bind so I could check out Crystal Caverns.  Tripped over a Frost Giant Scout -- blue con, and scouts are generally the lowest class of any given MOB, so I gave it a shot.  Beat on it for 30 seconds, was down to half health and hadn't made a damn dent in his HP bar.  Feign and wait a minute for the MOB to wander away and continue on my way to Thurg, laughing at how badly he had kicked my butt.<br><br>If you expect to be able to solo every MOB in the game, you're in for a serious disappointment.  If you properly use the benefits of the class, a monk can be a blast to play.<br><br>&nbsp;<br>Osano<br>Level 44 Human Monk<br>Tholuxe-Paells</td></tr>
